cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Mentori or the evaluation methodology in your own work, please cite both the paper and this software."
type: software
title: "Mentori: a locally-hosted agentic AI workspace for scientists"
abstract: >-
  Mentori is a multi-agent AI workspace that combines a chat interface,
  retrieval-augmented document analysis, and a Jupyter-based code execution
  sandbox. This repository accompanies the paper "Systematic Ablation Reveals
  Hidden Failures in Multi-Agent AI for Science" (Bianchi & Schokker,
  Nature Machine Intelligence 2026), which introduces a triple-triangulation
  evaluation methodology for retrieval-augmented multi-agent systems and
  applies it to over 36,000 individual evaluations spanning 200 scientific
  papers and 250 expert-curated questions.
